- I wonder if all state classes: eg: .active, .hidden .open etc should instead be data attributes? eg: data-state="open" data-focused="true" data-active="true" etc. 
This would be more verbose but also more descriptive and easier to read in the markup. 
It also allows for multiple states to be applied to an element without having to worry about class name conflicts. 
For example, an element could have data-state="open" and data-active="true" without having to worry about the order of class names or potential conflicts with other classes.

- Could we compress the server data attributes on the HTML?
It's currently JSON stringified and stored in a data attribute, which can take up a lot of space.

